What's the difference between a Data Lake and a Data Warehouse?

Data lakes store all types of raw data, which data scientists may then use for a variety of projects.

Data warehouses store cleaned and processed data, which can then be used to source analytic or operational reporting, as well as specific BI use cases.

FACT Table

Fact and Dim Tables

Fact tables contain numerical data, while dimension tables provide context and background information Effective Data Analysis and Decision-Making.

Fact Table Have Measures and Foreign Key

The Fact Table's Primary Key is usually a composite of the Foreign Key Columns, Although it can also be a Surrogate Key.

The Fact Table Contains Foreign Keys From The Dimension Tables.

Measures in Fact Table As Sum Avg Count Written in Data Analysis Expressions (DAX) Formulas.

Dimension Tables contain PK & Descriptions of the objects in a Fact Table.

The Star Schema Features:-

1>>Central Fact Table:Contains The Numerical Data Being Analyzed & Contains Foreign Keys to link to Dimension Tables.

2>>Dimension Tables.

3>>DB Denormalized Structure.

4>>Simple&Fast Queries>>By Joining The Fact Table With Dimension Tables.

5>>Aggregated Data>>(Sum, Average, and So On) in Power BI.

6>>Fast Performance & Fast Query Performance.

7>>Easy To Understand.
